-- Rain Improves Drought Conditions in Contiguous 48 States
-- B y   B r i a n   K .   S u l l i v a n
-- 2013-01-17T13:47:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-17/rain-improves-drought-conditions-in-contiguous-48-states.html
Rain last week improved drought
conditions across the contiguous 48 states, according to the
U.S.  Drought Monitor .  Drought covers about 58.9 percent of the 48 states, down
from 60.3 percent last week, according to the monitor in
Lincoln,  Nebraska . Areas in the grip of the most-severe drought
dropped to 6.3 percent from 6.7 percent a week ago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
